HEADWORD: Offhand
<hw>Off"hand`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Instant; unprepared;
ready; extemporaneous; unrehearsed; <as>as, an <ex>offhand</ex> speech;
<ex>offhand</ex> excuses; an <ex>offhand</ex> comment.</as></def> --
<def2><pos>adv.</pos> <def>In an offhand manner; <as>as, he replied
<ex>offhand</ex></as>.</def></def2>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

